# Legacy /getting-started.html → mkdocs Material doc.
# Real onboarding lives at /docs/getting-started/. Internal links across
# site/index.html, prescreen-demo.js, etc. still point at the .html path;
# this server-side 301 is the primary fallback. site/getting-started.html
# also exists as a meta-refresh stub for Cloudflare's static-first path.
/getting-started.html  /docs/getting-started/  301
/getting-started       /docs/getting-started/  301

# Per-program SEO pages live at /programs/{slug}-{sha1-6}.html (NOT
# /programs/UNI-xxx.html — UNI ids are unified_id only, the static
# filenames are derived from primary_name via utils/slug.py). The API
# now ships a `static_url` field so result cards can link directly to
# the canonical slug+hash file.
#
# The rules below catch legacy inbound traffic that targets the old
# /programs/UNI-xxxxxxxxxx[.html] pattern (old emails, blog posts, AI
# agent guess-the-URL) and bounces it to /programs/share.html, which
# resolves the id via /v1/programs/batch and renders a real card. The
# `UNI-` literal prefix in the source path means only UNI-shaped legacy
# requests get rewritten — slug-shaped /programs/{slug}-hash.html static
# files match an actual file on disk first and CF Pages serves them
# directly (file-system match wins over _redirects rules).
/programs/UNI-:uid.html  /programs/share?ids=UNI-:uid  302
/programs/UNI-:uid       /programs/share?ids=UNI-:uid  302

# NOTE: pretty URL rewrites removed — CF Pages auto-strips .html
# extension, so /pricing → site/pricing.html works natively. The
# explicit `/pricing → /pricing.html 200` rules caused an infinite
# redirect loop because CF Pages re-rewrote /pricing.html → /pricing.

# Device flow activation — RFC 8628 verification_uri.
# /go/ABCD-1234 → /go (page reads code from URL path or ?code= query).
# Bare /go works natively via CF .html stripping.
# S3 friction-removal landing — /go/upgrade?from=429 (linked from anon
# 429 body + X-Anon-Upgrade-Url header) is the anon → paid conversion
# entry point. Originally pointed at /go, but /go.html is the device-flow
# activation page that REQUIRES a user_code (e.g. ABCD-1234) — a 429-bouncer
# arriving from a curl/browser has no code, so they bounced. Now redirected
# to /upgrade which explains the 3 req/日 cap, points at pricing
# (#api-paid), and offers the device-flow path as a tertiary link for
# people who got there with a code. Query string is preserved by CF for
# funnel attribution.
/go/upgrade /upgrade  302
/go/:code /go?code=:code  302

