# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Jinja2 source-template leak guard.
#
# `site/_templates/*.html` are Jinja2 source files (program.html, qa.html,
# cross.html, prefecture.html, news_post.html, industry_program.html,
# prefecture_index.html). They are read by scripts/generate_*_pages.py and
# rendered into final HTML at /programs/*, /qa/*/*.html, /prefectures/*,
# /industries/*, /news/*. The raw .html files contain unrendered `{{ var }}`
# placeholders — if they leaked to the public domain, search engines would
# index broken markup. This rule marks the path gone (404) so Cloudflare
# Pages refuses to serve them even if they end up in the deploy artifact.
# Cloudflare Pages `_redirects` supports 200/301/302/303/307/308/404.
# We use 404 (resource permanently absent) instead of 410 because CF Pages
# rejects unknown status codes. /404 itself is the existing /404.html page.
/_templates/*  /404  404

# Standalone JSON-LD shards retired 2026-05-03. JSON-LD is now inlined
# in every /programs/<slug>.html page (one <script type="application/ld+json">
# per page). The /structured/*.jsonld URLs were only an alt-format duplicate
# of the HTML content, so the canonical page URL is the appropriate landing
# spot for inbound LLM crawlers.
/structured/*  /404  404
/sitemap-structured.xml  /sitemap-index.xml  301

